### Business Rules scenario checks (BFF)
### Base data
### Accounts:
### 128-9878-001 (cust 1, ACTIVE, 2000.00)
### 128-9878-002 (cust 1, ACTIVE, 11000.00)
### 128-9878-003 (cust 1, INACTIVE, 0.00)
### 128-9878-004 (cust 2, ACTIVE, 3000.00)
###
### Customers:
### 1 -> 487-978493
### 2 -> 500-100200
### 21 -> 442-100650
### 22 -> 980-104100
###
### Login identities:
### - account holder (cust 1): 487-978493 / password
### - account holder (cust 2): 500-100200 / password
### - teller: teller1 / password
###
### Set cookies after logging in through browser:
###   http://localhost:8080/oauth2/authorization/bank-auth

@bff = http://localhost:8080
@aliceCookie = BFF_SESSION=PASTE_ALICE_SESSION
@bobCookie = BFF_SESSION=PASTE_BOB_SESSION
@tellerCookie = BFF_SESSION=446173D19CDA65DCCD3AC7DF643A6ADB

################################################################################
### BR-A1: Every endpoint except GET /api/health requires valid authentication.
################################################################################

### A1.1 Health is public -> 200
GET {{bff}}/api/health
Accept: application/json

### A1.2 Accounts without auth -> 401
GET {{bff}}/api/accounts
Accept: application/json

### A1.3 Transfer without auth -> 401
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 10.00
}

################################################################################
### BR-A2: Deposits and withdrawals require teller role.
################################################################################

### A2.1 Deposit as account_holder -> 403
POST {{bff}}/api/deposits
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### A2.2 Withdrawal as account_holder -> 403
POST {{bff}}/api/withdrawals
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### A2.3 Deposit as teller -> success (200 from BFF wrapper)
POST {{bff}}/api/deposits
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "amount": 10.00
}

################################################################################
### BR-A3: Account status changes and transaction report require teller role.
################################################################################

### NOTE:
### These endpoints are not exposed in the current BFF controller set.
### If you add status/report endpoints later, use aliceCookie (expect 403)
### and tellerCookie (expect success) for role checks.

################################################################################
### BR-A4: account_holder may act only on own customer accounts.
################################################################################

### A4.1 Alice reading accounts -> should include only customer 1 accounts (001,002,003)
GET {{bff}}/api/accounts
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}

### A4.2 Alice transferring to Bob account -> 403
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-004",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### A4.3 Alice payment on Bob account -> 403
POST {{bff}}/api/payments
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: br-a4-unauthorized-payment-001

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-004",
  "amount": 25.00,
  "payee": "Utility Company"
}

################################################################################
### BR-A5: Teller transfer must stay within one customer (no cross-customer).
################################################################################

### A5.1 Teller cross-customer transfer (cust1 -> cust2) -> 403
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-004",
  "amount": 20.00
}

### A5.2 Teller same-customer transfer (cust1 -> cust1) -> success
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 20.00
}

################################################################################
### BR-A6: Referenced account/customer that does not exist returns 404.
################################################################################

### A6.1 Non-existent source account on transfer -> 404
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-999",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### A6.2 Non-existent destination account on transfer -> 404
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-998",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### A6.3 Non-existent account on payment -> 404
POST {{bff}}/api/payments
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: br-a6-missing-account-payment-001

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-999",
  "amount": 10.00,
  "payee": "Utility Company"
}

################################################################################
### BR-S1: No money movement on INACTIVE account. Return 422.
################################################################################

### S1.1 Deposit to inactive account -> 422
POST {{bff}}/api/deposits
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-003",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### S1.2 Withdrawal from inactive account -> 422
POST {{bff}}/api/withdrawals
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-003",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### S1.3 Transfer from inactive account -> 422
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-003",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### S1.4 Transfer to inactive account -> 422
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-003",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### S1.5 Payment from inactive account -> 422
POST {{bff}}/api/payments
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: br-s1-inactive-payment-001

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-003",
  "amount": 10.00,
  "payee": "Utility Company"
}

################################################################################
### BR-S2: INACTIVE account is visible in account reads.
################################################################################

### S2.1 Alice account list should still include 128-9878-003 with INACTIVE status.
GET {{bff}}/api/accounts
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}

################################################################################
### BR-V1: amount must be present, numeric, > 0, max two decimals -> 400
################################################################################

### V1.1 Deposit with missing amount -> 400
POST {{bff}}/api/deposits
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-001"
}

### V1.2 Deposit with zero amount -> 400
POST {{bff}}/api/deposits
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "amount": 0
}

### V1.3 Withdrawal with negative amount -> 400
POST {{bff}}/api/withdrawals
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "amount": -1.00
}

### V1.4 Transfer with more than 2 decimal places -> 400
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 10.123
}

################################################################################
### BR-V2: transfer requires destination account and it must differ -> 400
################################################################################

### V2.1 Transfer missing destination account -> 400
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### V2.2 Transfer where source == destination -> 400
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "amount": 10.00
}

################################################################################
### BR-V3: payment must include non-empty reference -> 400
################################################################################

### NOTE:
### Current API model uses "payee" as the required payment reference field.

### V3.1 Payment with missing payee/reference -> 400
POST {{bff}}/api/payments
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: br-v3-missing-reference-001

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "amount": 10.00
}

### V3.2 Payment with blank payee/reference -> 400
POST {{bff}}/api/payments
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: br-v3-blank-reference-001

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "amount": 10.00,
  "payee": "   "
}

################################################################################
### BR-V4: malformed JSON or unknown required fields -> 400
################################################################################

### V4.1 Malformed JSON body on transfer -> 400
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 10.00,
}

### V4.2 Wrong/unknown required field name for destination account -> 400
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountId": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 10.00
}

################################################################################
### BR-F1/BR-F2: insufficient funds and no negative balances (no overdraft)
################################################################################

### F1.1 Withdrawal with insufficient funds -> 422
### Expected: FAILED withdrawal transaction, no balance change.
POST {{bff}}/api/withdrawals
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "amount": 999999.00
}

### F1.2 Transfer debit leg with insufficient funds -> 422
### Expected: FAILED TRANSFER_OUT only, no TRANSFER_IN, no transfers row.
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 999999.00
}

### F1.3 Payment with insufficient funds -> 422
### Expected: FAILED PAYMENT transaction, no balance change.
POST {{bff}}/api/payments
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: br-f1-insufficient-funds-payment-001

{
  "accountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "amount": 999999.00,
  "payee": "Utility Company"
}

### F2.1 Verify balances never go below zero after failed debits
GET {{bff}}/api/accounts
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{aliceCookie}}

################################################################################
### BR-T1/BR-T2/BR-T3: transfer atomicity and outcome behavior
################################################################################

### T1.1 Baseline balances before successful transfer
GET {{bff}}/api/accounts
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}

### T1.2 Successful same-customer transfer -> success
### Expected: both legs COMPLETED, one transfers row, atomic commit.
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 15.00
}

### T1.3 Balances after successful transfer
### Expected: source decreased by 15.00 and destination increased by 15.00.
GET {{bff}}/api/accounts
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}

### T2.1 Transfer same source and destination -> 400 (BR-V2)
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 15.00
}

### T2.2 Transfer with inactive source account -> 422
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-003",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 15.00
}

### T2.3 Transfer with inactive destination account -> 422
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-003",
  "amount": 15.00
}

### T3.1 Insufficient funds transfer -> 422
### Expected: one FAILED TRANSFER_OUT, no transfers row, no credit leg.
POST {{bff}}/api/transfers
Accept: application/json
Cookie: {{tellerCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccountNumber": "128-9878-001",
  "toAccountNumber": "128-9878-002",
  "amount": 500000.00
}
